Cell C has announced the appointment of Zafar Mahomed as the company’s new Chief Financial Officer. Mahomed has over 20 years of finance and business experience, having worked in several multinational and listed organisation across various industries. “We are pleased to welcome Zaf Mahomed to Cell C,” said Cell C CEO Jose Dos Santos. “He brings extensive financial, management, and business experience to the role and we look forward to adding his expertise to Cell C’s leadership team.” Before joining Cell C, Mahomed was CFO for McDonald’s South Africa. Mahomed holds a Masters degree in Business Leadership from UNISA and is a qualified Chartered Accountant. “Telecommunications is a fast-paced and exciting industry and I look forward to joining the team at Cell C and putting my skills to work in such a vibrant and interesting business,” said Mahomed. Mahomed will begin is role as CFO at the beginning of December 2018.